article.description: Joshua Patton scored 22 points and pulled down 13 rebounds as Sacramento State pulled away from Southern Utah in the second half to post an 84-73 victory Thursday night.
article.headline: Patton leads Sacramento State past Southern Utah, 84-73
article.linkText: Patton leads Sacramento State past Southern Utah, 84-73
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. -- Joshua Patton scored 22 points and pulled down 13 rebounds as Sacramento State pulled away from Southern Utah in the second half to post an 84-73 victory Thursday night. The Hornets trailed at intermission, 33-32, but erupted for 52 second-half points to secure the win. Marcus Graves finished with 19 points and Izayah Mauriohooho-Le'afa added 18 points and dished six assists for the Hornets. Brandon Better had 19 points and Andre Adams contributed another 14 for the Thunderbirds (12-11, 7-7). The Hornets (11-11) are 5-8 in the Big Sky, but six of the team's 13 conference games were decided by six points or less, with Sacramento State going 1-5 in those games. In the first meeting between the teams, Sacramento State trailed by 28 points with 13:55 left in the game but roared back to have a chance to tie the game with :30 left only to lose, 76-71.
